reviews_data.review_text:
In one hour I was in and out.
Every one was kind and pleasant.
Very pleased with the PA and left feeling good that my fears were unfounded.
Before I could get home my prescription was waiting for me at my pharmacy.
I made my appointment on my iPhone and did not have to wait very long when I got there.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Janice, 
We are glad that you had a positive experience! Thank you for taking the time to leave a review.

reviews_data.review_text: My son was on a hunting trip in Bartlesville Oklahoma.  He has a rare illness that causes flares periodically when he has strep or is exposed to strep.  A lady doctor saw him and was very kind, thoughtful and patient with our son and his doctor that was relaying messages for treatment protocol.  We all could not have been more pleased with her skills and efforts to help on.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Michele, 
We are glad that you had a positive experience! Thank you for taking the time to leave a review.

reviews_data.review_text: Zac & nurse (didn’t get her name) were most helpful for a school sports physical for my daughter; both friendly & very thorough. Front staff very kind as well.  A great experience at Access! Relatively quick in & out also.  Highly recommend.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Sherry Vaughan,

Thank you for taking the time to rate and review your visit with us. We appreciate you choosing NextCare!

reviews_data.review_text: I cut my leg and of course I didn't know where to go.  I was overwhelmed at the excellent care I got.  Everyone was so kind and I mean EVERYONE.  The experience was exceptional and I would recommend them without hesitation.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Linda, 
We are glad that you had a positive experience! Thank you for taking the time to leave a review.

reviews_data.review_text:
The wait time is ridiculous.  Walked in when it opened for some simple blood work. Over an hour wait. They took somebody back who was 20 minutes late for their appointment instead of seeing the next patients who were already there
EDIT: the staff is incompetent.  I made an appointment OVER a WEEK ago all for pre employment for the second time. They did NOT communicate with the employment agency . I still waited an hour to get back even though I had an appointment.  I will be sure to tell my recruiter to NOT send any employees there. It was completely awful experience 2 times in a row.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Rebecka, 
We are sorry to hear about your negative experience at our clinic. We strive to provide exceptional service to all patients, and we are disappointed you left unhappy. Please know that we value your feedback and will use it to better our services. If you would like to discuss this matter further feel free to contact our Patient Liaison at wecare@nextcare.com. We hope that you get well soon.

reviews_data.review_text: My provider had the best bedside manner. She was at the same time honest, affirming, capable and reflective. I couldn't have asked for better care.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Bernadine, 
Thank you for your review! We hope if you are ever in need of care again you will come back to visit one of our clinics in the future.

reviews_data.review_text: Extremely friendly, helpful, knowledgeable staff. I liked that I could book an appointment time online. Hopefully I won't need urgent care again any time soon but if I do I'll definitely be coming here
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Crystal Granda,

Thank you for taking the time to rate and review your visit with us. We appreciate you choosing NextCare!

reviews_data.review_text: Frustrated. I went through all the trouble of loading everything on the app, while setting in their parking lot, to book a 7:15pm appt…just for the app to say, oh sorry, too late (this is at 7:10 mind you). We dart in the door at 7:10 and they say sorry, too late. There is only one person in line, which I saw on the app and in the waiting room. They close at 8PM!!! Guess not really. Grrr. I have a sick kid, so irritating!

reviews_data.review_text: I have had a few experiences with Access Medical- two virtual and one in-person. They offer the ability to set appointments and fill out the paperwork online in advance to minimize waiting to be seen. I have been seen by physicians and by a certified family nurse practitioner, and they all offered appropriate treatment options, did not rush through the appointments, were respectful and pleasant.  I appreciate the ability to be seen here when seeing  my primary care physician is not feasible.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Rosemary, 
We are glad that you had a positive experience! Thank you for taking the time to leave a review.

reviews_data.review_text:
Anytime I take myself, or the kids. It's an amazing experience. I do have to note. The weekend crew are alot happier than Monday's crew.
Other than that I will chose this over the E.R in Bartlesville
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Brittany, 
Thank you for your review! We hope if you are ever in need of care again you will come back to visit one of our clinics in the future.

reviews_data.review_text: Everyone was very friendly and professional. I made an appointment and got right in. I always go here when the need arises. Have always been satisfied.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Kathy, 
Thank you very much for your positive feedback. We truly appreciate you for choosing our clinic for your urgent care needs and taking the time to let us know how we are doing. We take pride in taking care of our patients. Hope you think of us in the future.

reviews_data.review_text: We have 10 people in our house, all but 3 are on antibiotics for strep, ear infections, and pneumonia.  My husband has had strep before, but they told him he has an infection that is untreatable in the hand-foot- mouth family!  He had to go elsewhere for re diagnoses.  It was strep!  He lost extra work time.  We have never had an issue there before, but I have strep now too.
